                    <div id="explain-cbt" style="display:none;">
                        <p>This tool is created to facilitate cognitive therapy.</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>In the Automatic Thoughts area, simply write out the automatic thoughts that cause you to experience a negative emotion. For example, you could write "These people think that I'm not good enough."</li>
                            <li>In the Cognitive Distortion area, select one of the cognitive distortions provided that explains why this thought is not true. Using the example from above, the cognitive distortion might be "Jumping to conclusions" and "Emotional Reasoning."
                                <li>In the Rational Response area, write down a response to this thought, setting it right. For example, "I don't know for certain what these people think of me, and it's actually better if I assume that they like me. It would be unfair to them for me to assume that they don't like me."</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p>Do this for 10-20 minutes a day.</p>
